@page "/privacy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - Snipster</PageTitle>

<main class="legal-page">
    <section class="legal-card">
        <a class="back-link" href="/"><i class="fa fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Snipster</a>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="effective-date">Effective date: May 6, 2026</p>

        <p>
            Snipster provides a code snippet management service that lets users create, organize, and share snippets and collections.
            This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have.
        </p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
            We collect account information such as your name, email address, password authentication data, registration status,
            and information needed to provide login and account management features.
        </p>
        <p>
            We also store content you create in Snipster, including snippets, collections, hashtags, programming language labels,
            sharing settings, and related metadata such as creation and modification dates.
        </p>

        <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>
            We use your information to create and manage your account, authenticate you, provide the Snipster service,
            save and display your snippets and collections, enable sharing features, send account-related emails,
            improve reliability, and protect the service from misuse.
        </p>

        <h2>Email Communications</h2>
        <p>
            We may send transactional emails, such as registration confirmation, password reset, and account-related notices.
            These emails are necessary for account security and service operation.
        </p>

        <h2>Sharing</h2>
        <p>
            Snipster lets you share snippets with other registered users. Shared users may be able to view snippet content
            and related collection information needed to display that shared snippet.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
            We may use trusted third-party providers for services such as email delivery, authentication, hosting, storage,
            analytics, or infrastructure. These providers process information only as needed to support Snipster.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
            We keep account and snippet data while your account is active or as needed to provide the service. If you delete
            your account, we delete your account and the snippets and collections you created, subject to reasonable technical
            processing time and any legal obligations.
        </p>

        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>
            We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information. No online service can guarantee
            absolute security, so you should use a strong password and keep your login credentials private.
        </p>

        <h2>Your Choices</h2>
        <p>
            You can update your account details, change your password, and delete your account from the account settings page.
            You can also control which snippets you share by updating their sharing settings.
        </p>

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
            Snipster is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the effective date on this page.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
            If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@snipster.co">support@snipster.co</a>.
        </p>
    </section>
</main>

<style>
    .legal-page {
        min-height: 100vh;
        padding: 48px 16px;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f5f7fa 0%, #e4e8ec 100%);
        color: #1f2933;
    }

    .legal-card {
        max-width: 920px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 36px;
        background: #fff;
        border-radius: 12px;
        box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    }

    .back-link {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        color: #0A3D91;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    .legal-card h1 {
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        color: #091E5D;
        font-size: 36px;
    }

    .effective-date {
        margin-bottom: 28px;
        color: #687786;
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    .legal-card h2 {
        margin: 28px 0 10px;
        color: #006666;
        font-size: 20px;
    }

    .legal-card p {
        margin: 0 0 14px;
        line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .legal-card a {
        color: #0A3D91;
    }

    @@media (max-width: 640px) {
        .legal-card {
            padding: 24px;
        }

        .legal-card h1 {
            font-size: 30px;
        }
    }
</style>
